The paper deals with the approximability of the Asymmetric Traveling Salesperson Problem (ATSP) on topologically restricted graphs, which involves the study of graph structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely categories. The paper also involves the use of dynamic programming and graph theory, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of solving ATSP exactly on graphs of pathwidth, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
